Kenya Airways on Friday treated its customers to entertainment and festive "goodies" ahead of Christmas celebrations on December 25. Passengers travelling through JKIA were treated to a song and dance by the airline's crew members as they waited for their flights.  KQ staff celebrating with children at JKIA ./COURTESY  "ChristmaswithKQ continues with more gifts, goodies and business class upgrades! It's all love and smiles here," KQ said via twitter. The younger ones were also not left out as the airline stuffed animals for them and a variety of merchandise.  The KQ cake./COURTESY "And a lovely cake to finally top off #ChristmaswithKQ ! We would like to wish all our esteemed guests a happy festive season," KQ said.  /COURTESY    Click here for the latest political news     